title: Unfair
author: elise
text: when a girl pretends to be your friend,  you can tell that your friendship is at the end.  so innocent,  so sweet,  from the first day we meet.  and then,  behind your back other friends lurk that you're not even aware of,  and that behavior i call unfair.  she lies and spreads rumors throughout the whole city,  and from the beginning i thought she was witty.  but little did i know she was a girl,  of unfairness.  she looks all cool,  with so many friends,  but inside she's striving.  she's striving to have everyone know her.  thinking that i could let such a person in my life,  how dare she keep disturbing me,  how dare she have so much unfairness.

title: Who you are
author: elise
text: who you are doesn't mean you have to be someone you're not.  you have to care and give a lot of thought.  everyone has their own unique way,  and they'll all be recognized one day.  there are people who don't know who they are,  and they know they won't go very far.  so believe in yourself that you can do it,  and just tell yourself that there's nothing to it.

title: Fly!
author: elise
text: what a beautiful thing in the sky,  all it strived for was only to fly.  with fragile wings,  and soft green eyes,  that beautiful thing just wanted to fly.  vibrant colors roamed the town,  that beautiful thing did not look down.  it brought a smile to everyone's face,  it soared with beauty,  pride,  and grace.  that beautiful thing was a sensation,  it even brought inspiration.  rotating and rotating around and around,  soon it spread cheer through all of the town.  twenty years later,  this story was told.  it helped people know that beauty was bold.
